{
  "text": "The restricted Laplacian L S is the submatrix of L restricted to S × S. And the restricted Green's function G S,β is defined as: G S,β (βI S + L S ) = I S , where β ≥ 0. Note that L S is positive definite [CITATION_1] , so G S,β is well-defined. The PageRank vector pr is defined as:",
